{"ts":"2026-06-12T16:11:16.056Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-dzcx"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Dedup private Levenshtein implementations onto shared OSA helper"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Two files reimplement plain Levenshtein instead of importing the shared OSA Damerau-Levenshtein helper (src/core/shared/levenshtein.ts, levenshteinDistanceWithinLimit): (1) src/core/store/item-store.ts:193 'levenshtein' used by buildDidYouMeanSuggestions for item-ID did-you-mean; (2) src/core/extensions/extension-capability-aliases.ts:61 'levenshteinDistance' used by suggestKnownExtensionCapability. Besides duplication, both copies miss the transposition-cost-1 upgrade shipped in PR #78, so ID/capability typo suggestions are weaker than flag/command suggestions. Fix: replace both with the shared limited helper (item-store uses a dynamic limit max(3, len/2) so call with that limit; capability suggester is unbounded best-match, can iterate limits or add a non-limited export). Evidence: grep -rln levenshtein src/ shows 7 importers of the shared module + these 2 private copies."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Task"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["audit-2026-06-12","dedup","refactor"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-12T16:11:16.056Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-12T16:11:16.056Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"a3c2d8f52fe8db3306e52b8c5c33638c8354606cd472ca1deae3b1c9b80a7135","message":""}
